description: From Latin nautilus, from Ancient Greek ναυτίλος (nautílos, “paper nautilus, sailor”).

entries.meaning: A marine mollusc, of the family Nautilidae native to the Pacific Ocean and Indian Ocean, which has tentacles and a spiral shell with a series of air-filled chambers, of which Nautilus is the type genus.
examples: He was still prepared to go on collecting all that life could offer, like a chambered nautilus patiently adding new cells to its slowly expanding spiral.

entries.meaning: A kind of diving bell that sinks or rises by means of compressed air.
